9 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) The following definitions apply throughout
10 As used in this section,
11 (1) "Camera" means a camera, a video camera, a device that
12 captures a digital image, or any other type of video recording
13 device.
14 (2) "peep" means
15 (A) any looking of a clandestine, surreptitious, prying, or
16 secretive nature. or
17 (B) using a concealed camera with the intent of capturing an
18 intimate image (as defined by IC 34-21.5-2-1).
19 (3) "Private area" means the naked or undergarment clad genitals,
20 pubic area, or buttocks of an individual.
21 (b) A person:
22 (1) who knowingly or intentionally:
23 (A) peeps; or
24 (B) goes upon the land of another with the intent to peep;
25 into an occupied dwelling of another person; or
26 (2) who knowingly or intentionally peeps in or into an area where
27 an occupant of the area reasonably can be expected to disrobe or
28 is actually expected to disrobe, including:
29 (A) restrooms;
30 (B) baths;
31 (C) showers; and
32 (D) dressing rooms;
33 without the consent of the other person, commits voyeurism, a Class B
34 misdemeanor.
35 (c) However, The offense under subsection (b) is a Level 6 felony
36 if
37 (1) it is knowingly or intentionally committed by means of a
38 camera; or
39 (2) the person who commits the offense has a prior unrelated
40 conviction under this section.
41 (d) A person who:
42 (1) without the consent of the individual; and
