21 (B) in a location that is not visible from an area:
22 (i) open to the general public; or
23 (ii) where a member of the general public has the right to be;
24 commits remote aerial voyeurism, a Class A misdemeanor.
25 (h) The offense under subsection (g) is a Level 6 felony if the person
26 has a prior unrelated conviction under this section or if the person:
27 (1) publishes the images, photographs, or recordings captured;
28 (2) makes the images, photographs, or recordings captured
29 available on the Internet; or
30 (3) transmits or disseminates the images, photographs, or
31 recordings captured to another person.
32 SECTION 12. IC 35-45-4-5.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
33 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
34 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5.5. (a) The following definitions
35 apply throughout this section:
36 (1) "Camera" means a camera, a video camera, a device that
37 captures a digital image, or any other type of video recording
38 device.
39 (2) "Private area" means the naked or undergarment clad
40 genitals, pubic area, or buttocks of an individual.
41 (b) A person who, without the consent of the individual, records
42 an image of the private area of an individual by means of a camera
2026 IN 1253—LS 6829/DI 149

